rComments: He has a massive knowledge on his subjects and tests are not hard if you study from past exams.

The professor is very clear in explaining the concepts to the students. The pace of the course is EXTREMELY slow to allow for all students to be able to follow. The final and the midterms tend to be easy but have a lot of very tedious questions where you can make potential errors.
Unclear, not helpful, and doesn't care about the course. Very poor prof.

This guy is smart. He taught MIE335 very well. He gives a summary of what we did in the last lecture which makes it easier to follow what's going on in the class. Even though he is a genius, I felt that there is an element of laziness in him. He spent 1 entire lecture on distributing the midterms. We only had 3 HW assignments and 3 super easy labs.

words arent enough to express his level of coolness.. i cant wait to be taught by him agian..
